commitmsg: Added unit tests.
Don't reset status to IDLE if reboot command fails.
Try to rmdir before mkdir during sd card test.
Updated to use new sendemail API.
Patch smtplib in Python versions under 2.6.3. Changed to standard coding style.
Do nonblocking reads when reading from subprocess when polling.
Changed rm -rf to rm -r when deleting profile, since the latter is not a valid on android.
Do status update even if disabled-phone mail fails.
Make sure we can cd to sd card as well as making a dir there.
Catch socket errors when sending email.
Check for errors when rebooting. Force ping on next iteration after reenabling.
Replaced all DISCONNECTED states with DISABLED. Simplified PhoneWorker.disable_phone(). Try to recover phone after ping fails.
Fixed trigger_runs.py for nightlies. Fixed exception when unable to obtain device root.
Use echo instead of ps as heartbeat since the output is less.

trigger_runs.py can trigger jobs for tinderbox builds and from local files.
Also log all stdout and sterr from adb commands, cached builds expire after
one day, phone worker does heartbeat every 15 minutes instead of every minute,
verify cached builds and redownload if bad zip, removed some unused imports,
and a couple tiny fixes.
Reboot command now uses more robust recover_phone() method. Removed check for drawing != 0 since it is never reported.
More clean-up of trigger_runs.py. Immediately go back to IDLE when a job completes.

Added build cache. Fixed infinite loop in tcp request handler. Simplified
job creation and triggerjobs command. Added disable and reenable commands.
Check sdcard before starting jobs. Always retry 3 times. Changed s1s2test
to record time of first occurrence of throbstart/stop.
Fixed typo.
More logging.
Added DISABLED state. Include IP in phone status.
If two AndroidErrors occur during the same test, disable the phone.
Added timeouts for some adb commands, after which the device is rebooted.
Fixed retry loop; reboot is tried 3 times, and each test tried twice. Email when phone is disabled.
Increased reboot timeout to 300 s.
More logging and status info. Moved build installation to PhoneWorker.
Moved TCP classes into AutoPhone. Implemented status command.
Removed some debug print statements.
Added script to trigger runs.
Removed deprecated pulsebuildmonitor option.
Updated pulse build monitor usage.
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/ctalbert/autophone
Catch all exceptions while running tests and report them. Note time that autophone is launched and terminated.
Reboot phones and try job again if a device manager error is encountered.
Trailing slash in profile path not needed.
Typo in profile path
Correctly push profile and runbrowserprofile.sh to phone
Latest changes from mcote
Enabled pulse build monitor.
Renamed config file to avoid clobbering it all the time.
Merge branch 'master' of github.com:markrcote/autophone
Merge pull request #2 from ctalbert/master
Merge pull request #1 from ctalbert/master
Merge.
Can create, push, and use custom profiles. Some pulse support.
Fix bug with retry logic - it wasn't killing the browser for each retry

Merge pull request #1 from ctalbert/master

See what you think - 30s delay between tests and a retry of 3 attempts per job (in case we get 0s)
Make my if statement pretty
Adding a delay between jobs of 30s and a retry in case we get 0s during a test
Log adb-not-in-path warning only once per process. Workers log to their own files. Implemented status command. Added --no-reboot option.
Allow specification of IP address as command-line option. Reboot phones in separate processes.
Initial commit.

Bug 1063886 - Autophone - paydown technical debt, r=mcote.
* Make pyflake clean.
* switch to jot.
* Remove armv6 since it is no longer supported
* fix runjob vs. run_job inconsistency in tests.
* move test config file reading to PhoneTest constructor.
* add missing import ConfigParser
* remove PhoneTestMessage.JSONEncoder
* Use AutophoneOptions object to encapsulate command and ini configuration data instead of user_cfg dictionary.
* Use PhoneData object instead of phone_cfg dict to encapsulate phone data.
* Use BuildMetadata object instead of build_metadata dict to encapsulate build data.
** Change BuildMetadata's attributes to be less verbose: build_dir to dir, build_type to type, androidprocname to app_name, blddate to date.
* PhoneTestMessage/update_status
** Move phonetest.PhoneTestMessage to phonestatus, eliminate status_cb from PhoneTest constuctor
** Move phonetest.PhoneTestMessage.* status values to phonestatus.PhoneStatus
** change PhoneTestMessage signature to use phone_status, message arguments
** change worker status_update and phonetest set_status to update_status.
** Pass PhoneData to PhoneTestMessage, optionally pass BuildMetadata.
* PhoneTest
** Use PhoneWorker.setup_job/teardown_job to set the worker_subprocess as an attribute on PhoneTest
** Add PhoneTest.build property to return PhoneTest.worker_subprocess.build
* Remove build_metadata and worker_subprocess arguments where available as attributes.
* Make sure to use phone_status kwarg on PhoneWorker.update_status
* Remove redundant build.id from s1s2tests update_status messages.
* Fix undefined use of proc in PhoneWorkerSubProcess._check_device.

Bug 969518 - Autophone - attempt to use reverse tethering so we can use ethernet over usb instead of wifi, r=mcote.

* autophone.ini.example
** Update with usbnet examples.
* autophone.py
** Do not lower case registration url data as device serial numbers
   are case sensitive.
** Make the host port distinct for each ppp connection.
** Add debug logging about usbnet set up and catch errors from
   calling usbnet.sh. Terminate Autophone and send email notification
   if an error occurs calling usbnet.sh.
** In Autophone.stop, call stop on the workers before calling shutdown
   on the Autophone instance. This along with the change to worker.py,
   helps prevent deadlocks when shutting down the server.
* worker.py
** Call terminate on worker process when stopping the worker.
* usbnet.sh
** Fix typo in usage.
** Implement a shell function wait_for_device using adb get-state
   which will time out and return an error after 30 seconds.
** Restrict usbnet to devices where we can run adbd on device as
   root so we can create the ppp device on the phone. Terminate
   with a non-zero exit code if adb root is not supported by a device.
** If we have udev rules set up we do not need suid adb except
   for when creating the ppp devices.
** Explicitly turn off deflate and bsd compression on the ppp
   connection.
